{{Quote|Minions of Xendor! Good thing we're gettin' outta here!|Han Solo, to Bria Tharen|<ref name="TPS" />}}
"'''Minions of Xendor'''" was a phrase used as an expletive that referred to the [[Legions of Lettow]] and their leader [[Xendor]].

==History==
{{Quote|Now who in the Name of Xendor are you, and why were you askin' about me?|Mako Spince, to Han Solo|<ref name="THG" />}}
[[File:BattleOfColumus-BoS.jpg|thumb|right|230px|The phrase "Minions of Xendor" referred to those who supported Xendor during the First Great Schism]]
The phrase "Minions of Xendor" referred to<ref name="CSWE" /> the [[Legions of Lettow]], those who followed [[General/Legends|General]] [[Xendor]], a [[Kashi Mer]] [[Exile (punishment)/Legends|exile]]<ref name="EGW">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref> and former [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]],<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> during the [[First Great Schism]] of [[24,500 BBY]].<ref name="JvS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref>

During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], the expression "Legions of Xendor" was used by [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Halagad Ventor]] while on a [[Battle of Skye|mission]] to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Skye/Legends|Skye]].<ref name="SkyeWalkers" />

During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Period]], the phrase was commonly used among [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]], such as by [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]],<ref name="TPS" /> [[Mako Spince]], [[Bria Tharen]], [[Falan Iniro]],<ref name="THG" /> and [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]].<ref name="RD" /> The expression was often used by Solo when he was surprised by something.<ref name="CSWE" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Mention of Lyn's lover "Xendor and his minions" was a bit of tongue-in-cheek fun. Prior to this, Xendor was little more than an unspecified noun making up part of one of Lando's preferred exclamations&hellip;|Abel G. Peña|<ref name="Blog">{{Blog|abelgpena|84|The Emperor's Pawns Endnotes, Part 4: Mistress of Teräs Käsi}}</ref>}}
The phrase "Minions of Xendor" first appeared in the [[1997]] novel ''[[The Paradise Snare]]'', the first volume of ''[[Star Wars: The Han Solo Trilogy]]'' authored by [[A. C. Crispin]].<ref name="TPS" /> The [[2001]] article ''[[The Emperor's Pawns]]'', co-written by [[Abel G. Peña]] and [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and published in [[Star Wars Gamer 5|''Star Wars Gamer'' 5]], later revealed that "Xendor and his minions" were the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] responsible for the First Great Schism,<ref name="TEP">{{GamerCite|5|The Emperor's Pawns}}</ref> a conflict originally mentioned in the [[1996]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] [[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 0|''Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith'' 0]].<ref name="TGAotS0">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 0|''Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith'' 0]]</ref> The [[2005]] reference book ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'', co-written by [[Daniel Wallace]] and [[Kevin J. Anderson]], identified Xendor's followers as the Legions of Lettow.<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>

